    "body": "Yes, 10% rings a bell. The replacement transaction needs to be better. How can a node determine which (out of two) transactions to use, if they are equally 'good'? \r\nFrom the original description, it sounds like you are erroneously reusing nonces, thus creating \"replacement transactions\". That seems to be the core issue, not that you cannot reliably replace transactions in 0-cost chains. \r\nChanging that is not just a matter of coding -- how would it even work? What would be the logic determining what transaction is 'better' ?",
